node.text: To all our readers,Please don’t scroll past this. This Wednesday, for the 1st time recently, we interrupt your reading to humbly ask you to support Wikipedia’s independence. Only 2% of our readers give. Many think they’ll give later, but then forget. If you are an exceptional reader who has already donated, we sincerely thank you.

If everyone reading this donated $2.75, we could keep Wikipedia thriving for years. The price of a cup of coffee is all we need. One donation may seem small, but when millions of readers each give, we can do great things.
We’re a nonprofit, and the 58 million articles that compose Wikipedia are free. Without reader contributions, big or small, we couldn’t run Wikipedia the way we do.
That’s why we still need your help. We are passionate about our model because at its core, Wikipedia belongs to you. We want to make sure everyone on the planet has equal access to knowledge.
If Wikipedia provided you $2.75 worth of knowledge this year, please take a minute to secure its future by making a donation. Thank you.

Please select an amount (USD). The average donation is $16.36. Many first-time donors give $2.75. All that matters is that you're choosing to stand up for free, open information; and for that, you have our gratitude.
